Coding Standards
  set of guidelines, best practices and programming styles that developers followed when writing source code for a project.

Parts of Coding Standards
  * Reasonable Variable Name
    int age = 22;
    int userAge = 35;

  * Proper Method Name
    void CheckInternetConnection(){
      //fancy networking code
    }

  * Comments
    //this is a comment

Commenting Styles
  * Single-Line Comments
      //a bool to check if user is logged in
      bool isUserLoggedIn = true;

  * Multiline Comments
    /*these methods are respomsible for storing user data and connecting to the database.*/

  * XML documentation comments
    ///<summary>
    //This method is very cool
    ///</summary>
    void CoolMethod(){
      //cool code
    }


